# Ruby / Bundler
# Deliberate library-gem policy: a published gem resolves its dependencies from
# the gemspec's version constraints, so we intentionally do NOT commit
# Gemfile.lock or pin .ruby-version. CI (ci.yml) instead tests the whole
# supported range — Ruby 3.2, 3.3, 3.4 and 4.0 — which a committed lock/pin would
# hide. (This is Bundler's standard "gem vs. application" lockfile guidance.)
*.gem
*.rbc
.bundle/
.ruby-version
.ruby-gemset
vendor/bundle/
Gemfile.lock
.bundle-vendor/

# metaclean's own outputs (never want these committed)
*_clean.*
*_clean_*.*
*.bak
*.metaclean.tmp.*
*.cleaned.*
*.qpdf.tmp.*

# Editor / OS
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.claude/
CLAUDE.md

# Test / build artefacts
/tmp/
/coverage/
/pkg/
/doc/
.yardoc/
